The paper presents a deep neural network framework for modeling complex high dimensional stochastic dynamic systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the application of the framework to biological systems, which falls under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses deep generative models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
